text: Agdistis obstinata is a moth in the family Pterophoridae. It is known from South Africa, Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda, Saudi Arabia, Yemen and Ethiopia.New Species and Records of Plume Moths of the Genus Agdistis Hübner, 1825 (Lepidoptera: Pterophoridae, Agdistinae) from Southern Africa ==References== Category:Agdistinae Category:Moths described in 1920 Category:Moths of Africa Category:Insects of Uganda Category:Moths of the Middle East Category:Insects of Ethiopia Category:Insects of Tanzania
